## <a name="bin"></a> Install the cf CLI Using a Compressed Binary

This section describes how to install the cf CLI using a compressed binary. You can install the cf CLI using a compressed binary on Windows, Mac OS X, and Linux operating systems.

For more information about downloading and installing a compressed binary, see the [Installers and compressed binaries](https://github.com/cloudfoundry/cli#installers-and-compressed-binaries) section of the cf CLI repository on GitHub.


## <a name="verify"></a> Verify Installation

To verify the installation of the cf CLI, do the following:

1. Close and reopen the command prompt. Or, open a new tab in the command prompt.

1. Run the following command:

	```
	cf --help
	``` 
	If your installation was successful, the cf CLI help listing appears.


## <a name="uninstall"></a> Uninstall the cf CLI

This section describes how to uninstall the cf CLI. There are different methods for uninstalling the cf CLI depending on the installtion method.

### <a name="uninstall-pkg"></a> Package Manager

This section describes how to uninstall the cf CLI if you installed the cf CLI with a package manager.

To uninstall the cf CLI, follow the instructions specific to your package manager.

### <a name="uninstall-installer"></a> Installer

This section describes how to uninstall the cf CLI if you installed the cf CLI with an installer. Follow the instructions in this section that are specific to your operating system.

To uninstall the cf CLI on Mac OS X, do the following:

1. Delete the binary `/usr/local/bin/cf`.

1. Delete the directory `/usr/local/share/doc/cf-cli`.

To uninstall the cf CLI on Windows, do the following:

1. Navigate to the **Control Panel** and click **Programs and Features**.

1. Select `Cloud Foundry CLI VERSION` and click **Uninstall**.

### <a name="uninstall-binary"></a> Binary

This section describes how to uninstall the cf CLI if you installed the cf CLI with a binary.

To uninstall the cf CLI, do the following:

1. Navigate to the location where you copied the binary.

1. Delete the binary.
